---
title: Scroll-Triggered Reveal
description: "Elements fade and slide up as they enter the viewport using CSS scroll-driven `animation-timeline: view()`."
slug: scroll-triggered-reveal
cssFile: scroll-triggered-reveal.css
explanation: "`animation-timeline: view()` links animation progress to an element's position within its nearest scrollable ancestor. `animation-range: entry 0% entry 45%` means the animation plays while the element moves from 0% to 45% into the visible area — so it's fully revealed before reaching the center. Each list item animates independently, creating a natural staggered cascade as you scroll through them."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="demo-scroll-triggered-reveal">
	<div class="scroll-hint">↓ scroll to reveal</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-teal">⚡</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">Scroll-driven animations</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Link animation progress directly to scroll position — no JavaScript, no IntersectionObserver.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-coral">🎨</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">CSS custom properties</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Dynamic theming, animations, and calculations powered entirely by CSS variables.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-violet">📦</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">Container queries</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Responsive components that adapt to their container's size, not the viewport.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-sky">🔗</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">CSS nesting</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Write scoped, composable styles inside each other — native Sass-style syntax.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-orange">📐</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">Subgrid</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Nested grids that align to their parent's tracks, making complex layouts trivial.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="reveal-item">
		<div class="reveal-icon reveal-icon-yellow">✨</div>
		<div class="reveal-body">
			<div class="reveal-title">@starting-style</div>
			<div class="reveal-desc">Animate elements from their initial state when they first appear in the DOM.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="scroll-container">
  <div class="reveal-item">...</div>
  <div class="reveal-item">...</div>
  <div class="reveal-item">...</div>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.reveal-item {
  animation: streveal-up linear both;
  animation-timeline: view(block);
  animation-range: entry 0% entry 45%;
}

@keyframes streveal-up {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(32px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
